 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.33","title":"[audit][test] Decouple Trace capture from implicit stderr printing in TestLogger","description":"TestLogger::new(TestLogLevel::Trace) currently flips verbose=true, so asking for maximal event capture also causes immediate stderr emission from library test-support code. Make verbosity explicit instead of coupling it to Trace, add regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteCliff","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:56:03.345624674Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:16:32.925143002Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:16:32.925119328Z","close_reason":"Completed: TestLogger trace capture no longer implies verbose stderr output; file-local rustfmt and UBS clean, rch cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed, focused rch test passed, clippy remains blocked only by unrelated src/channel/oneshot.rs lint frontier","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.33","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T01:56:03.345624674Z","created_by":"WhiteCliff","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","title":"[audit][evidence] Make evidence_sink timestamps deterministic","description":"src/evidence_sink.rs currently stamps emitted EvidenceLedger entries with SystemTime::now() in non-test helper functions, which makes scheduler/cancel/budget evidence nondeterministic and bypasses the runtime's explicit time capability. Replace the ambient wall-clock stamping with a deterministic timestamp source, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaHollow","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:03:28.921765757Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:27:04.869450201Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:27:04.869422099Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","evidence"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:03:28.921765757Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2458,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Validation currently blocked by shared compile frontier in src/service/reconnect.rs (lifetime error at line 271 during rch-backed evidence_sink test run); patch in src/evidence_sink.rs is formatted and awaiting rerun once lib compiles again.","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:13:47Z"},{"id":2459,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.34","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Implemented deterministic sink-owned evidence timestamps in src/evidence_sink.rs: added EvidenceSink::next_evidence_ts(), backed JsonlSink and CollectorSink with AtomicU64 sequences, switched scheduler/cancel/budget emit helpers off SystemTime::now(), and added regression test emit_helpers_use_deterministic_timestamp_sequence. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/evidence_sink.rs ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-evidence-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-evidence-clippy cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-evidence-regression cargo test -p asupersync --lib emit_helpers_use_deterministic_timestamp_sequence -- --nocapture ✅ (1 passed). Repo-wide cargo fmt --check still fails only in unrelated shared files (src/channel/oneshot.rs, src/combinator/rate_limit.rs, src/http/h1/codec.rs, src/net/websocket/frame.rs, src/sync/notify.rs, src/transport/aggregator.rs, src/web/request_region.rs).","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:26:59Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.35","title":"[audit][service] Make Oneshot transition safely if inner call panics","description":"ServiceExt::oneshot takes the request out of its Ready state before invoking service.call(req). If that synchronous call panics while constructing the inner future, a caught unwind leaves the Oneshot future stuck in Ready with request=None instead of moving to a terminal state. Patch src/service/service.rs so the panic path leaves Oneshot internally consistent, add a focused regression that catches the first panic and verifies the future is no longer poisoned with the wrong invariant, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CyanDesert","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:08:08.146146717Z","created_by":"CyanDesert","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:18:12.319860801Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:18:12.319834712Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.35","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:08:08.146146717Z","created_by":"CyanDesert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
